{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17648177","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17648177"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T20:50:59+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T20:50:59+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18297"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"18297","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/18297"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"11015"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"80167"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"11015","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/11015"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18297"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"65444"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4931"},{"type":"tags","id":"4941"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"25567"},{"type":"contributions","id":"25569"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"80167","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/80167"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EThe hamstring muscle group consists of three muscles in the posterior compartment of the thigh that cross both the hip and knee joints.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following movements are the semimembranosus and semitendinosus muscles primarily responsible for?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Internal rotation of the leg when the knee is flexed","External rotation of the leg when the knee is flexed","Abduction of the hip","Adduction of the hip","Extension of the knee"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe semimembranosus and semitendinosus muscles are located in the posterior compartment of the thigh and are part of the hamstring muscle group.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe semimembranosus and semitendinosus muscles are primarily responsible for \u003Cstrong\u003Einternal rotation of the leg when the knee is flexed\u003C/strong\u003E. They also play a role in knee flexion and hip extension.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect options can be explained:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EExternal rotation of the leg when the knee is flexed\u003C/strong\u003E - This is performed by other muscles such as the biceps femoris\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EAbduction of the hip\u003C/strong\u003E - This is primarily performed by the gluteus medius and minimus\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EAdduction of the hip\u003C/strong\u003E - This is primarily performed by the adductor group of muscles\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EExtension of the knee\u003C/strong\u003E - This is primarily performed by the quadriceps femoris group\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["The semimembranosus and semitendinosus muscles are part of the hamstring group located in the posterior thigh.","These muscles are primarily responsible for knee flexion and hip extension.","The semimembranosus and semitendinosus also contribute to internal rotation of the leg when the knee is flexed."],"references":["Sud, A., \u0026 Ranjan, R. (2018). Textbook of Orthopaedics, -E-Book. Elsevier Health Sciences","Singh, V. (2018). Textbook of Anatomy Abdomen and Lower Limb; Volume II (Vol. 2). Elsevier Health Sciences","Cantrell AJ, Imonugo O, Varacallo M. Anatomy, Bony Pelvis and Lower Limb: Leg Bones. [Updated 2023 Aug 14]. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Islan